	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> " He was a monk of the 14th century and was consecrated as\n                  a deacon by \n                  \n                     ʾabuna \n                     Yāʿqob. \n                  He became a monk after the soldiers abducted his wife. \n                  He took the monastic habit from \n                  \n                     ʾabbā \n                     ʾIyǝsanano ʾƎgziʾ. He was the spiritual father of Sāmuʾel of Dabra Halleluyā.\n               " .
